{"description":"{quote}\r\nThe class PreparedStatementAndResultSetCheck throws a StackOverflowError when the SQL request is built with the string concatenation operator. Only with the following syntax : var \u003d var + string; \r\nIn this case, there is a infinite loop between 3 PreparedStatementAndResultSetCheck methods : handleVariableUsedAsQuery, getNumberQuery, handleVariableUsedAsQuery\r\n\r\nWith different + operator syntax : var \u003d string1 + string2; \u0026 var +\u003d string; there is no StackOverflowError\r\n{quote}\r\n\r\nFor code example see: https://groups.google.com/d/msgid/sonarqube/95c65fdc-3338-4ce5-98ca-bf2a5ef52d14%40googlegroups.com?utm_medium\u003demail\u0026utm_source\u003dfooter\r\n\r\n","component":"SonarJava","component_version":"3.9"}